Stone Island _ Autumn Winter '021'022
41131 DAVID LIGHT-TC WITH MICROPILE
Hooded jacket made of a lightweight tela woven with Japanese star-shaped cross-section polyester/polyamide yarns with a polyester micro pile layer inside. It is assembled and then dyed under pressure at 130°C, with the addition of an anti-drop agent. During the garment dye process, the heat radically transforms the material’s hand and structure. The resulting garments combine an industrial appearance with a unique feel.
#StoneIsland #GarmentDyed

Stone Island _ Autumn Winter '021'022
41527 SOFT SHELL-R_e.dye® TECHNOLOGY WITH PRIMALOFT® INSULATION TECHNOLOGY
Blouson made of a 3-ply performance material with an 8000 MM water column. The polyester stretch canvas outer face is woven with yarns using e.dye® Waterless Color System™ technology, the innovative yarn colour saturation system which reduces by 85% the use of water and by 90% the chemicals used in the dye process. The fabric is laminated to a breathable, water- and wind-proof inner membrane. The material structure lends great flexibility and comfort. The garment is padded with an inner layer of #PrimaLoft®, an exclusive blend of ultra-small diameter 70% recycled fibres resulting in superior thermal performance. It delivers the highest warmth-to-weight ratio of all synthetic insulations.
#StoneIsland
